_sText:
kz bhop awf3l is the successor to the critically acclaimed and widely loved bhop awful, often considered the best map in existence, as well as the legendary and mysterious bhop awful2. 
This map seeks to uphold the same standards as both these maps, and lives very well up to this huge responsibility.
- _"Why do you keep making these maps, Aux?" -ShotgunBFFL, faste hops_
Some believe this map is made by God himself. Some people are right. Seemingly nothing can be improved on this masterpiece of a map, combining science and religion into a single map, made for YOUR enjoyment!
And enjoy it I hope you do!! ~Aux

(PS. The map should be doable on any setting, other than 400u/s cap... I'm not sure about that one)

bhop awful2, a map that should not have been. 
_(At least if you ask the game engine, I swear to god, I had more problems compiling this than bhop aux a9)_

Either way, I don't really have any fancy words this time, I simply hope you enjoy the map. Looking at if I can continue to find things I want to improve or optimize, but I have to stop somewhere, and this was it. If there's anything I forgot, feel free to give me a poke. 
~Aux

Oh, and...
>_The bhop awful series has gone too far up hill!_
- Kazman

*DISCLAIMER*


This map contains scenery and music with sounds that may be disturbing for some, it has no jumpscares or anything exaggerated, but just a word of warning for anyone with caution for dark, small places and potentially disturbing sounds.

With no other option, you jump into a hole that leads to an abandoned asylum, a bhop map with a ''horror'' theme, something never seen in bhop before. Can you beat the challenge and find your way to the light ?

Custom soundscapes and textures
Moody lighting
Average difficulty
First map on source. Map time is around 17-20 seconds on average. If there is any bugs lmk and ill fix.

This map is a bhop_orbital, bhop_celestial and bhop_dimensional merged together (in that order, zone orbital as the start and dimensional as the end). Only has a couple of cps because I wanted to keep the linear feeling of the maps and I personally find them easy to run anyway, I know there won't be a lot of players that want to run this, but I'm publishing it anyway because I think a one shot run would look cool (if you do get a nice run pls show me ty xx)

Some parts of Celestial/Dimensional have been removed/changed to suit the high-speed gameplay (you dont lose your speed between the 3 maps) 

Be sure to play with a maxvelocity of at least 5k.

A short little 40 sec technical map with a 10 second strafe bonus. Took me way too long to make, and I sort of made it to clear my head after spending months on my other map. Mostly just a break from that arduous task. 

Lighting is mostly a combinaton of some blue glass, and some skybox. Originally it was just blue glass and white lights, but that made some of the stages incredibly dark.

Stages: 8
Bonus: Yes
Time: 20 sec - 1 min
Difficulty: Easy - Medium (Bonus is kinda hard tho)



A couple skips here and there in the main map, one big skip in the bonus, but you need like 600+ SSJ to do it without prespeed.

Enjoy the map, if not then feel free to delete it.

EDIT: Fixed the teleport on last level, thanks Alex.

The map didn't take me that long, its better than my first one obviously since I actually know what I'm doing now (still open to debate), but the map itself I believe looks pretty cool for my standard.
I don't know why I named it asscrack was too lazy to think of a fitting name so asscrack it is!

This is a slight edit to the original bhop_arcane_v1 by panzer. This version has minimal gameplay changes, only a few tweaks to triggers and such to make them more consistent. This version of the map was made to be speedrun friendly as rng has no place in bhop. The name was voted on by several people in the SourceJump discord, so dont complain.

My first bhop map, bhop_arcane. This is a very long bhop map which goes through multiple themes. Overall there are 5 stages with secrets. There is also multihopping on this map so players can bhop on the same platform multiple times. Good luck!

Features:
 - 5 long stages
 - 5 secret buttons (1 per stage) which unlock bonus content at the end of the map
 - Pistols with trails at the end of each stage
 - Hidden weapons throughout the map
 - High speed bhop raceways (grassy underground area, neon area, and snow area)
 - Waterfall slides (sewer area)
 - Long multihop platforms with obstacles (neon area)
 - Launchers (snow area)
 - At the end of the map:
 --- Scouts
 --- Long jumps
 --- 9 weapons (3 must be unlocked with secret buttons)
 --- Bonus with special weapon at the end (bonus must be unlocked with secret buttons)

If you were a beta tester and want to be added to the list, ask me on steam.

This is a map I started a long time ago but never finished it. Tioga and I intended on making a full map in a week but after realizing that it would never be finished in that amount of time, we just stopped working on it. This will likely never been finished since it's just not worth the time investment for me anymore, but I may make some shorter maps in the future.

Soundscapes are meant to be included, but I decided not to make another version just to add the soundscapes since this version is already on a bunch of servers.

This map is intended to be played on auto bhop, but I think it is possible to beat on normal bhop.
